node.text:
The “ Eye of God” or The Helix Nebula is a planetary nebula located in the constellation Aquarius, at about 650 light years from the Earth. Discovered by Karl Ludwig Harding in the early 19th century, Helix is one of the closest of all the bright planetary nebulae. 

The central star of the Nebula, a white dwarf remnant of the star that exploded about 10,000–12,000 years ago, gives the resemblance of an eye.

@SpaceSpot for more Astronomy & Science
Space store 👉 @spacespotshop 

📸: @NASA

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by SpaceSpot Astronomy & Science on August 01, 2021. May be an image of sky.

node.text:
What is the first thing you see? 💀

Located at the edge of a large molecular cloud in Monoceros some 5,000 light years away.

The lovely, symmetric shape is sculpted by the winds and radiation from its central cluster of hot young, O-type stars. Stars in the energetic cluster, cataloged as NGC 2244, are only a few million years young, while the central cavity in the Rosette Nebula, is about 50 light-years in diameter.

@SpaceSpot for more Astronomy & Science
Space store 👉 @Spacespotshop

📸: @curtismorgan

node.text:
Strawberry 🍓 Moon 🌕 
Swipe to zoom in!

Follow & Explore @SpaceSpot 🔭
Space Shop: @Spacespotshop 

Named after the “June bearing” strawberries ready to be gathered around this time of the year. Tonight’s Moon is the second and last super Moon this year. A Moon can qualify as Super when it’s 224000 miles (~360000 Km) away from Earth. It should be noted then, that this second super Moon almost falls in the “Super” category since it’s 224,600 miles away. On contrary, the Moon is the farthest from Earth in Apogee, which is approximately 238,855 miles (384,400 km) away. 

Other names for the Full Moon of June are: Blooming Moon which is indicative of the flowering season, and the Green Corn Moon. 

📸: @rami_astro

May be an image of text that says 'NASA astronaut Frank Culbertson was the only American not on the planet when the 9/11 terrorist attacks occurred. This is one of the photos he took. His morning call started with Mission Control telling him "Frank, we're not having a very good day down here on Earth"'.

node.text:
At the time, the astronauts did not have live TV or Internet at the space station. But Culbertson saw on the astronauts' map that the orbiting outpost was over southern Canada and about to pass over New England. He grabbed a camera and moved to a window in the Russian portion of the space station, where he had a clear view of the dark smoke over New York.

@SpaceSpot for more Astronomy & Science
Space store 👉 @Spacespotshop

Via: @astropicfuturism

node.text:
This is a breathtaking photo of the Mount Sinabung eruption 🌋

This violent eruption spewed ash up to 7500 meters into the air. Villages were coasted in ash, and residents were given facemaks by the government and advised to stay indoors to avoid breathing in dangerous particles. Thankfully, no injuries or fatalities were caused by the eruption. 

Mount Sinabung is a Pleistocene-to-Holocene stratovolcano of andesite and dacite in the Karo plateau of Karo Regency, North Sumatra, Indonesia, 40 kilometres from the Lake Toba supervolcano.

Captured: Feb 19, 2018

📸: Perspectaweather
